</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="38" pageNumber="637" type="activity">
<paragraph blockId="38.[1366,2574,2023,2808]" pageId="38" pageNumber="637">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1367,1603,2535,2569]" pageId="38" pageNumber="637">Activity patterns.</emphasis>
The 
<taxonomicName authority="Gerbil" authorityName="Gerbil" box="[1685,1921,2535,2569]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Gerbillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="38" pageNumber="637" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rosalinda">Rosalinda Gerbil</taxonomicName>
is probably nocturnal and terrestrial, digging burrows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1369,2308,2614,2648]" pageId="38" pageNumber="637" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="38.[1366,2574,2023,2808]" box="[1369,2308,2614,2648]" pageId="38" pageNumber="637">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1369,2069,2614,2648]" pageId="38" pageNumber="637">Movements, Home range and Social organization.</emphasis>
